🟢 STEP 1: Create Project Folder
Go to Desktop
Create new folder:
WEBAGILE
Open this folder in VS Code
🟢 STEP 2: Create index.html
Right click → New File → index.html
Paste:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>CI/CD Demo</title>
<style>
body{
text-align:center;
font-family:Times New Roman;
background-color:#af0d0d;
}
h1{
color:#0ef777;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>CI/CD Pipeline Working</h1>
<h2>Deployed using Jenkins + Docker + Kubernetes</h2>
<p>This webpage is automatically deployed using a CI/CD pipeline.</p>
</body>
</html>

👉 Save

🟢 STEP 3: Create Dockerfile
New File → Dockerfile
Paste:
FROM nginx:latest
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
EXPOSE 80

👉 Save

🟢 STEP 4: Build Docker Image

Open terminal in that folder:

docker build -t html-demo .
🟢 STEP 5: Run Docker (Test)
docker run -p 8081:80 html-demo

👉 Open browser:

http://localhost:8081

✅ If page opens → continue

🟢 STEP 6: Create Docker Hub Repo

Go to 👉 Docker Hub

Login
Click Repositories
Click Create Repository
Enter:
Name → html-demo
Public ✅
Click Create
🟢 STEP 7: Push Image to Docker Hub

Run in terminal:

docker tag html-demo abishar26/html-demo
docker login
docker push abishar26/html-demo
🟢 STEP 8: Create deployment.yaml
New File → deployment.yaml
Paste:
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: html-demo
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: html-demo
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: html-demo
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: html-demo
        image: AbishaR26/html-demo:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80

---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: html-demo-service
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: html-demo
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 80
    nodePort: 30010
🟢 STEP 9: Start Kubernetes
minikube start

Check:

kubectl get nodes
🟢 STEP 10: Deploy to Kubernetes
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml

Check:

kubectl get pods

👉 Wait until Running

🟢 STEP 11: Open Website
minikube service html-demo-service

✅ Browser opens 🎉

🟢 STEP 12: Push Code to GitHub

Go to 👉 GitHub

Create repo → ci-cd-demo

Then run:

git init
git add .
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/ci-cd-demo.git
git push -u origin main
🟢 STEP 13: Setup Jenkins

Open:

http://localhost:8080
🔹 Create Pipeline
Click New Item
Name → pipeline
Select Pipeline
Click OK
🔹 Paste this (EDIT USERNAME + GITHUB LINK)
pipeline {
 agent any

 environment {
 DOCKER_IMAGE = "AbishaR26/html-demo"
 }

 stages {

 stage('Clone Code') {
 steps {
 git branch: 'main',
 url: 'https://github.com/yourusername/ci-cd-demo.git'
 }
 }

 stage('Build Docker Image') {
 steps {
 bat 'docker build -t %DOCKER_IMAGE% .'
 }
 }

 stage('Push Image') {
 steps {
 bat 'docker push %DOCKER_IMAGE%'
 }
 }

 stage('Deploy to Kubernetes') {
 steps {
 bat 'kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml'
 }
 }

 }
}
